  "text": "## Prometheus Metrics Exposition Pattern: Kubernetes vs Grafana\n\n### Overview\nBoth Kubernetes (v1.32.0) and Grafana (v11.4.0) use the Prometheus client_golang library to expose internal metrics. However, they implement significantly different architectural patterns for metric registration, collection, and exposition.\n\n### Kubernetes Metrics Infrastructure\n\n**Architecture Pattern:** Kubernetes uses a hierarchical, stability-aware metrics registry system designed for long-term metric versioning and deprecation management.\n\n**Core Components:**\n\n1. **Registry Implementation** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/registry.go`):\n   - `KubeRegistry` interface defines the contract for metric registration and collection\n   - `kubeRegistry` struct wraps Prometheus registries with version-awareness and deprecation tracking\n   - Supports `Register()` and `MustRegister()` methods that check metric stability levels\n   - Implements `Registerable` interface for collectors that support version-aware registration\n   - Tracks hidden and disabled metrics separately via `hiddenCollectors` and `disabledMetrics` maps\n\n2. **Legacy Registry Pattern** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go`):\n   - Provides a global `defaultRegistry` instance that all components use\n   - `Handler()` returns an HTTP handler instrumented via `promhttp.InstrumentMetricHandler()` and `promhttp.HandlerFor()`\n   - Automatically registers process and Go runtime collectors via `collectors.NewProcessCollector()` and `collectors.NewGoCollector()`\n   - `HandlerWithReset()` variant supports DELETE method for test-driven metric resets\n\n3. **Collector Framework** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/collector.go`):\n   - `StableCollector` interface extends `prometheus.Collector` with stability awareness\n   - `BaseStableCollector` provides a base implementation of custom collectors\n   - Implements `Describe()` and `Collect()` methods that filter by registration state\n   - Supports `DescribeWithStability()` and `CollectWithStability()` for custom metric hiding logic\n\n4. **HTTP Endpoint Registration** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/metrics.go`):\n   - `DefaultMetrics` struct implements route installation pattern\n   - `Install()` method registers `/metrics` endpoint via `c.Handle(\"/metrics\", legacyregistry.Handler())`\n   - Calls `register()` function that triggers metric registration in various subsystems:\n     - `apimetrics.Register()` - API server metrics\n     - `cachermetrics.Register()` - Storage cacher metrics\n     - `etcd3metrics.Register()` - etcd3 backend metrics\n     - `flowcontrolmetrics.Register()` - Flow control metrics\n     - `peerproxymetrics.Register()` - Peer proxy metrics\n     - `handlersmetrics.Register()` - Request handler metrics\n\n5. **Modular Metric Registration** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/prometheus/controllers/metrics.go`):\n   - Each subsystem defines its own metrics in isolated packages\n   - `Register()` function uses `sync.Once` to ensure one-time registration\n   - Metrics are registered to `legacyregistry.MustRegister()` during init\n   - Example: `controllerInstanceCount` gauge tracks running managed controllers\n\n6. **SLI Metrics** (`staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/prometheus/slis/routes.go`):\n   - Separate `/metrics/slis` endpoint for Service Level Indicator metrics\n   - Uses registry-based pattern via `metrics.HandlerFor(Registry, metrics.HandlerOpts{})`\n   - Supports both standard and reset variants\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n- Stability-level tracking: ALPHA, BETA, STABLE with deprecation version support\n- Version-aware registration ensures old metrics are hidden when deprecated\n- Global `legacyregistry` provides centralized collection point\n- Separation of concerns: metrics registered at package init time across subsystems\n- Both `/metrics` (primary) and `/metrics/slis` (SLI-specific) endpoints\n\n### Grafana Metrics Infrastructure\n\n**Architecture Pattern:** Grafana uses a simpler, application-centric metrics system with explicit service injection and direct Prometheus client usage.\n\n**Core Components:**\n\n1. **Instrumentation Service** (`pkg/server/instrumentation_service.go`):\n   - Standalone HTTP service running on separate port (default: `:3000`)\n   - `instrumentationService` struct wraps an HTTP server\n   - `newInstrumentationServer()` creates a minimal HTTP mux with single endpoint: `router.Handle(\"/metrics\", promhttp.Handler())`\n   - Uses `promhttp.Handler()` directly without custom instrumentation\n   - Lifecycle managed via `services.BasicService` with start/stop handlers\n\n2. **Metrics Declaration** (`pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go`):\n   - All metrics are declared as global variables with Prometheus types:\n     - `MInstanceStart prometheus.Counter`\n     - `MPageStatus *prometheus.CounterVec`\n     - `MApiStatus *prometheus.CounterVec`\n     - `MProxyStatus *prometheus.CounterVec`\n     - Many others for alerts, dashboards, datasources, rendering, etc.\n   - Metrics initialized in `init()` function with `prometheus.NewCounter()`, `prometheus.NewCounterVec()`, `prometheus.NewGauge()`, `prometheus.NewSummary()`, etc.\n   - All metrics use `ExporterName = \"grafana\"` as namespace\n   - `initMetricVars(reg prometheus.Registerer)` function calls `reg.MustRegister()` for all metrics\n   - `SetBuildInformation(reg prometheus.Registerer, ...)` creates dynamic build info metrics\n   - `SetEnvironmentInformation(reg prometheus.Registerer, ...)` creates environment info metrics\n\n3. **Metrics Service** (`pkg/infra/metrics/service.go`):\n   - `ProvideService()` performs dependency injection setup\n   - Calls `initMetricVars(reg)` and `initFrontendMetrics(reg)` to register all metrics\n   - `InternalMetricsService` runs optional Graphite bridge for metric forwarding\n   - `ProvideRegisterer()` returns `legacyregistry.Registerer()` - uses Kubernetes' legacy registry internally\n   - `ProvideGatherer()` returns wrapped `multiRegistry` combining Kubernetes and Prometheus gatherers\n   - `addPrefixWrapper` decorator ensures all non-prefixed metrics get \"grafana_\" prefix\n   - `multiRegistry` combines multiple gatherers with duplicate detection\n\n4. **Custom Metric Utilities** (`pkg/infra/metrics/metricutil/utils.go`):\n   - `NewCounterStartingAtZero()` - initializes counters with zero observation\n   - `NewCounterVecStartingAtZero()` - initializes counter vectors with all label combinations at zero\n   - `buildLabelSets()` - generates Cartesian product of label values\n   - Label name sanitization via `SanitizeLabelName()`\n\n5. **Frontend Metrics** (`pkg/infra/metrics/frontendmetrics.go`):\n   - `initFrontendMetrics()` registers browser-side metric histograms\n   - `registerFrontendHistogram()` pattern for consistent histogram registration\n   - Maps metric names to recorder functions in `FrontendMetrics` map\n   - Metrics include: boot load time, first paint, JS/CSS load timing\n\n6. **Dependency Injection** (`pkg/infra/metrics/wireset.go`):\n   - Uses Google `wire` framework for DI\n   - `WireSet` provides: ProvideService, ProvideRegisterer, ProvideGatherer\n   - `WireSetForTest` provides test variants with fresh registries\n\n**Key Characteristics:**\n- Simple, flat metrics structure with global variables\n- Direct use of `prometheus.NewCounter()` family without custom wrappers\n- Single `/metrics` endpoint via standard `promhttp.Handler()`\n- Dependency injection via `wire` framework\n- Automatic prefix wrapping via `addPrefixWrapper`\n- Reuses Kubernetes' `legacyregistry` for underlying registry\n- Explicit metric initialization in `init()` blocks and service providers\n\n### Comparison Summary\n\n| Aspect | Kubernetes | Grafana |\n|--------|-----------|----------|\n| **Registry Model** | Custom `KubeRegistry` with version/stability awareness | Direct Prometheus registry (with Kubernetes' legacyregistry underneath) |\n| **Metric Declaration** | Lazy initialization in package init; uses `Registerable` interface | Global variables initialized in `init()` function |\n| **Registration Mechanism** | Pluggable `Register()` functions across subsystems; called at route install time | Centralized in `initMetricVars()` and `initFrontendMetrics()` |\n| **Deprecation Support** | Built-in: stability levels, version hiding, hidden metrics tracking | Not implemented; all metrics are permanent |\n| **Collector Pattern** | Custom `StableCollector` base class for complex collectors | Direct prometheus.Collector usage via library |\n| **HTTP Endpoint** | `/metrics` (main) + `/metrics/slis` (SLI-specific) | Single `/metrics` via `promhttp.Handler()` |\n| **Instrumentation** | Auto-instrumented via `promhttp.InstrumentMetricHandler()` | Default promhttp instrumentation |\n| **Metric Prefix** | Subsystem-specific; explicitly set in metric options | Automatic \"grafana_\" prefix wrapper |\n| **Service Architecture** | Routes installed into existing API mux | Separate HTTP service on dedicated port |\n| **Dependency Injection** | Package-level registration functions | Google `wire` framework with providers |\n\n### Exposition Pattern Summary\n\n**Kubernetes Pattern:**\n1. Multiple subsystems register metrics via `Register()` functions called during route installation\n2. Metrics collected by global `defaultRegistry` with stability/deprecation awareness\n3. HTTP handler created via `promhttp.InstrumentMetricHandler()` wrapping `promhttp.HandlerFor()`\n4. Supports custom collector frameworks via `StableCollector` interface\n5. Designed for API server and cluster component monitoring\n\n**Grafana Pattern:**\n1. All metrics declared globally and initialized in `init()` blocks\n2. Metrics registered during service startup via `initMetricVars()` and `initFrontendMetrics()`\n3. HTTP handler via standard `promhttp.Handler()` in isolated service\n4. Metrics wrapped with automatic \"grafana_\" prefix for consistency\n5. Simplified for application monitoring without version/deprecation complexity"
